An Asynchronous WebSocket Client Library for Scala. As simply as

     val w: Websocket = new Websocket();

     w.open("ws://localhost")
        .listener(new MessageListener() {
            override def onMessage(message: String) {
                // Do something
            }
        })
        .send("Hello World")
        .listener(new MessageListener() {
            override def onMessage(message: Array[Byte]) {
                // Do something
            }
        })
        .send("Hello World".getBytes)

Build the workspace and you are all set! Artifacts will be in Maven Central soon!


